cs.CC, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.GT 

The paper deals with the Parallel Repetition Theorem for certain projection games, which involves concepts from computational complexity (cs.CC) and information theory (cs.IT). The use of graphs and their properties, such as expanders and bi-regular extractors, suggests categories such as cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) and cs.CG (computational geometry). Finally, the mention of l1 and l2 guarantees on induced distributions from large subsets suggests a connection to game theory (cs.GT).
